    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-02-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4b/301</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilbur</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d1fn2">In telegrams dated Feb. 17, 6 p.m., the information
                        contained in this letter was communicated to the Embassies in France, Great
                        Britain, Italy, and Japan, with instructions to convey it to the respective
                        Governments.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">29440–178:17S</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I take pleasure in advising you that this
                    Department has completed the work of the scrapping of vessels required to be
                    demolished under the Treaty Limiting Naval Armament.</p>
                <p>Under the provisions of the Treaty the Battle Cruisers <hi rend="italic"
                        >Lexington</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Saratoga</hi> are being converted into
                    airplane carriers and the Battleship <hi rend="italic">North Dakota</hi> is
                    being retained as a target.</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis D. Wilbur</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
